    <div class="page">
      <h1 class = "panel">Vintage Simulator (VSIM)</h1>

      <div class="panel intro">
        Vintage Simulator is a (currently 100% FREE) custom libretro front-end (sharing zero code with RetroArch)
        with the following features:

        <ul>
          <li>Implements most of the libretro API</li>
          <li>Run several emulators at the same time</li>
          <li>Full Lua scripting API</li>
          <li>3D graphics and sound</li>
          <li>Easily load most 3D models such as 3DS or OBJ</li>
          <li>Bullet Physics engine</li>
          <li>Plugins</li>
          <li>Includes LOVE plugin (for UI screens in separate windows 
              or generating textures etc.)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="panel gallery">
        <ul class="gal">
          <li>
            <img src="manycores.png"/>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class = "panel content">With VSIM you can create your own virtual collection of vintage computers, consoles, and software,
        all represented in 3D.  Or, using the physics and memory access features, build a spacecraft with 
        flight control software written in C64 assembler.  Set up anything you can imagine by importing
        libretro cores, your own 3D models, and writing Lua code.</div>

      <div class="panel content"><a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/runvnc/VSIMdocs"><h2>Documentation</h2></a> 
      </div>

      <div class="panel content">
        <em>Note: VSIM is currently in a "pre-pre alpha" development stage.  Documentation is incomplete and there
          may be various bugs.</em> Unzip into c:\vsim (if the path has spaces then plugins won't install)

        <a href="vsim0619.zip"><h2>Direct Download (Windows)</h2></a>
      Start with command "vsim.exe 5 0.0025" to specify slower mouselook unless you are using a trackpad like me.
      </div>

    </div>
